==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tasse
<hw>Tasse</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>tassette</ets>.]</ety> <def>A piece of armor for the thighs,
forming an appendage to the ancient corselet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Usually the <xex>tasse</xex> was a plate of iron
swinging from the cuirass, but the skirts of sliding splints were also
called by this name.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tassel</ent>⟦br⟧
